Peel and finely chop the @carrot{1} into tiny cubes (less than ½cm cubes if
possible). Chop the @celery stick{1} into tiny cubes too. Chop the very bottom
and the leafy top from the @leek{1}. Slice the leek into ½cm discs. Finely
chop as much @red chilli{½} as you dare.

Pinch the @thyme{5} stalks between your thumb and index finger and run your
fingers along the stalk to strip off the leaves. Remove the @sage{2} leaves
from their stems and roughly chop.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add
the carrot, celery, leek, chilli, thyme and sage to the pan. Add a good pinch
of @salt{pinch} and cook gently for around ~{8%minutes} until soft.

> Tip: Turn the heat down if the ingredients start to brown off.

Place each @British chicken breasts{2} between two sheets of #clingfilm{}.
Use a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} to whack the chicken.

> Tip: You want the chicken to be less than 1cm thick all over.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{a splash} in another #non-stick frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. Once hot, add in your chicken, skin-side down and cook for
around ~{4%minutes} on each side. Season both sides with a pinch of @salt{pinch}
and @black pepper{} whilst cooking.

> Tip: The chicken is ready when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Thoroughly rinse and drain the @green lentils{1}. Add them to your pan of
vegetables with a splash of @water{a splash}, the @chicken stock pot{½} and the
@creme fraiche{1}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few grinds of @black pepper{}
(taste and add more if needed). Cook for ~{1%minute} or two until everything is
warm. Spoon the mixture onto plates and top with your cooked chicken.